 :tx/rationale "Create task: PERF-4b: Reflexive FEGH — daemon runs generate_bridge_hypotheses on its own runtime knowledge graph. Before answering any external query, the daemon examines its self-model for disconnected clusters and generates bridge hypotheses. This is FEGH-1 applied reflexively — the simplest possible test case for bridge hypotheses because we control every variable and have immediate ground truth. APPROACH: (1) After capability census (PERF-4a) and runtime history load from W-alpha, build the daemon's self-model as a knowledge graph: capabilities, runtime metrics, cache states, performance measurements. (2) Run spectral_partition on this graph to find communities. (3) For each pair of weakly-connected communities, generate a bridge hypothesis via project_delta. (4) Surface the top bridge as a reflexive insight: 'SELF: store-cache (implemented, 1.4s) and routing-computation (uncached, 10s) are disconnected. Bridge: caching routing results would connect these.' (5) This output appears in braid status as a reflexive guidance line. VALIDATION: The daemon's first bridge hypothesis on our 70K store should identify the routing-cache gap — the exact insight that took us 1 hour to discover manually. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Daemon generates at least 1 reflexive bridge hypothesis. (B) The routing/caching bridge is identified. (C) Bridge hypotheses are recorded in W-alpha with item_type=reflexive. (D) Hypothesis outcomes calibrate via the same ledger as project hypotheses. DEPENDS-ON: PERF-4a, FEGH-1. FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/routing.rs"
